{
  "text": "where RE p,r and RE q,r are relative entropies of the same form as Equation (2), comparing the column and background distributions (p and q, respectively) to r = (p + q)/2. Again, sequential residues are included to improve predictive power. As with WPE, a window width of seven, which is used herein, has been determined to be ideal [CITATION_1] . We compute JSD and WPE scores using software provided by the Singh lab.",
